The susceptible–infectious–recovered–deceased (SIRD) [19, 21] is modified version of the SIR model (Sect. 2.1). In this model, there are separate compartments for the deceased and recovered individuals. The time-dependent functions S(t), I(t), R(t), and D(t) are the total number of susceptible individuals, the total number of infected individuals, the total number of recovered individuals, and the total number of deceased individuals, respectively, and N is the total population, which is assumed to remain constant over the study. Different compartments of the SIRD model are shown in Fig. 2. Using this model, we studied time dependence functions like the recovery rate (\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
